    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The six not-assessed factors are justified as not required at MRL 2 per the credibility assessment plan. Validation evidence demonstrates RH < 1.0 for all five operating conditions, satisfying the primary acceptance criterion. Discretization error (GCI max 3.2%), model form uncertainty (±8% on RH index), and boundary condition sensitivity (±5.3% on RH index) are all within acceptable bounds. The compound uncertainty budget (RSS combination of all quantified sources) yields a total simulation uncertainty of ±9.7% on the RH index, which does not alter the acceptance decision given the margin to the RH = 1.0 threshold. The credibility assessment team unanimously accepts this simulation as fit for the intended regulatory purpose.",
